i## Backup and restore	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iTo back up container data, I use Duplicati. It lets you	/	tilde.team	70
iencrypt data and manage retention very easily via a web	/	tilde.team	70
iinterface.	/	tilde.team	70
hDuplicati	URL:https://duplicati.com/	duplicati.com	443
i	/	tilde.team	70
iThese backups can then be restored on my old computer.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
i## Monitoring	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iTo keep abreast of service status, I've opted for Uptime	/	tilde.team	70
iKuma, which will alert me via Discord when a service is down	/	tilde.team	70
ifor n seconds.	/	tilde.team	70
hUptime Kuma	URL:https://uptime.kuma.pet/	uptime.kuma.pet	443
i	/	tilde.team	70
iI also have a Prometheus and Grafana stack that lets me	/	tilde.team	70
icollect metrics on the system and on Docker containers. As	/	tilde.team	70
ifor Uptime Kuma, I'm alerted by Discord according to limits	/	tilde.team	70
idefined for RAM and available storage space, for example.	/	tilde.team	70
hPrometheus	URL:https://prometheus.io/	prometheus.io	443
hGrafana	URL:https://grafana.com/	grafana.com	443
hUptime Kuma	URL:https://uptime.kuma.pet/	uptime.kuma.pet	443
i	/	tilde.team	70
